Your AI isn’t a mind reader.

A lot of people think all AI models work the same. They assume a vague prompt will give roughly the same result everywhere.

But that’s not true. Every model is built differently. They’re trained on different data and follow different rules. A prompt that works on one might fail on another. They don’t read between the lines. They match patterns. (1/2)
